Police have this evening arrested two people suspected of vandalizing the Standard Gauge Railway line in Mtito Andei, Makueni County.  The duo; Michael Mbevi, a scrap metal dealer, and Nicodemus Kyove, a lorry driver are accused of destroying the SGR line this week on Monday, causing a two-hour delay.  “Mbevi, the scrap metal dealer alongside the lorry driver, Kyove were arrested and are in custody as an investigation to arrest their accomplices is intensified,” the National Police Service said.  Authorities recovered railway line blocks, twenty-two pieces of Gauge blocks, and one fish plate, that they say were “part of a haul being loaded into a waiting lorry at a scrap metal yard in Mtito Andei.”  The duo will be charged with economic sabotage and terrorism-related offenses.  Cuban woman says football star Maradona raped her as teenager, 'stole my childhood'  Mai Mahiu population to rise as infrastructural development pick  SGR passenger service recovers after Covid hit  Tsavo West: Rich in animals and history Any person caught committing unlawful acts or acts of sabotage along railway lines will face the law, police have said.       Hits and Misses of the SGR project as it marked 4 years since the launch of its operations  Reli ya SGR Tanzania: Reli ya umeme kuanza kutumika Agosti, ni reli ya umbali wa kilomita 205  Kenya to take over SGR from Chinese operator | Press Review By Muriithi Mugo | 1 day ago By Stephen Nzioka and Phillip Muasya  | 1 day ago By Phares Mutembei | 1 day ago By Muriithi Mugo | 2 days ago